deck: Common Gotham fish poisoned by the Joker - causing them to develop deformed Joker-like smiles.
description:
History

Once ordinary Gotham sea life, the Joker Fish were first created when the Joker poisoned Gotham's waters with his venom. The toxin was engineered to not affect humans directly, instead he attempts to patent and market his line of Joker Fish to the public, thus gaining royalties for every fish sold.

However, when he attempts to copyright his creation, a terrified patent officer by the name of G. Carl Francis tells him he can't patent a natural resource. The Joker, outraged, threatens to kill Carl at midnight, and despite the best efforts of the Gotham Police Department he succeeds. Joker then announces that he will kill a second bureaucrat if he doesn't get his way.

Batman deduces that the Joker's next target is bureaucrat Thomas Jackson. Batman disguises himself as Jackson in his home in order to protect the official.

However, Joker sends in Jackson's house cat who he poisoned with his Joker Fish. The cat, knowing who his real owner is, attacks Jackson scratching and poisoning him. Although Batman cannot save Thomas in time, he is able to track down and confront the Joker, thus he never receives the patent.

In the non-canon Damian: Son of Batman, a booby trapped Joker Fish is responsible for the supposed death of Batman.

Other Media

Joker Fish also appear in the episode of Batman: The Animated Series; The Laughing Fish, based on the Detective Comics issue of the same name.

deck: A device created by a Batman of an alternate world.
description:
Considered by the Batman of Zur-En-Arrh to be the most valuable object in his utility belt.

History

Silver age:

Originally, the Bat-Radia was created by the scientist Tlano, the Batman of Zur-En-Arrh. It's purpose was to discharge electronic molecules that caused a controlled disturbance in the atmosphere. This rendered useless the motors of jet-cars used by Tlano's fleeing enemies. Although it was only effective in the atmosphere of Zur-En-Arrh, Tlano gave the Bat-Radia to the original Batman as a keepsake of one of his most bizarre adventures.

Modern Age:

During the Batman R.I.P story line, the Bat-Radia was re-introduced as a simple Am/Fm radio Batman modified to send a signal giving him control of Arkham Asylum's security systems.

Other Media

The Bat-Radia also appeared in the animated episode of Batman: Brave and the Bold - "The Super-Batman of Planet X!"

deck: The A.R.G.U.S. Key was a device designed to track the location of every A.R.G.U.S. base and allow access to its most secret installations which was normally in the hands of the United States President.
description:
The A.R.G.U.S. Key was created shortly after the formation of A.R.G.U.S. following Darkseid's invasion of Earth. It was only the formation of the Justice League that saw the forces of Apokolips being defeated. In the aftermath, A.R.G.U.S. was created under orders from the President of the United States of America. The organization was intended to support the superheroes efforts but it was also meant to monitor them in case the Justice League ever went rogue. Afterwards, the organization was established with many facilities and staff to support them. This saw the creation of the A.R.G.U.S. Key that allowed the tracking of all their facilities and access to the more restricted installations. These included the Black Room, Red Room, Green Room, the Circus and the Wonder Room. The Key itself was kept in the care of the American President and only used in the most extreme of circumstances.

During the events of Forever Evil, the Crime Syndicate was responsible for seemingly killing the Justice League. This saw the Secret Society of Super-Villains attempting to take control of the now vulnerable world. Among the survivors was Steve Trevor who headed A.R.G.U.S. and after the decimation of their headquarters he decided to retrieve the Key. At this point, the Secret Society was attacking the White House in order to take the President hostage. Trevor and a team were dispatched to rescue the President where he used it to put the Commander-in-Chief into the Green Room for safety. With the Key, Steve later gained access to the Wonder Room in order to consult the Delphi Mirror on Wonder Woman's fate.

He later used the key to open the Circus after it went into lockdown during the Crime Syndicate's control of the planet. This allowed Trevor to meet A.R.G.U.S. agent Dale Gunn who provided him a telepath that allowed him to determine the means in finding Wonder Woman which was the Lasso of Truth that was in Cheetah's hands.
name: A.R.G.U.S. Key

deck: The Godseed is an artifact and given by the Bridgewalker to his successor where their powers evolve in preparation for custodianship of the Seed Planet
description:
The Godseed was created by the custodian of the Seed Planet who bore the title of Bridgewalker. These individuals were protectors of a world that served as the center of the web that encompassed both the Green and the Red. The web led to the emergence of groups such as the Parliament of Trees and the Parliament of Limbs who in turn selected avatars to champion their causes on their respective planets. However, even these Totems were not fully privy of the Bridgewalker who was able to survive for thousands of years. Despite this great lifespan, they were capable of growing old and dying but before that time they selected avatars from worlds who were brought to the Seed Planet. These beings could be avatars of the Green or Red but were required to fight one another. The survivor would then be selected as a replacement for the Bridgewalker when they died. To boost their power, they were needed to devour the Godseed that evolved them to the point where they could bear the responsibilities of that role.

Buddy Baker was brought to the Seed Planet by the reigning Bridgewalker during the crisis when Brother Blood under the patronage of the King of Limbs had usurped Earth's Red. Baker was the only survivor of the various contenders and told of the history of the Seed Planet and that Buddy was to be the next Bridgewalker. However, he desired to return to Earth to save his daughter Maxine Baker from Brother Blood. Ultimately, the Bridgewalker allowed Baker to return to his homeworld but on the condition that when the custodian died that Buddy would need to replace him. This was a non-negotiable deal and Baker was required to swallow the Godseed that would evolve him for the task in the future.
name: Godseed
